The paper deals with the application of unsupervised learning approaches, and in particular of clustering techniques, for the analysis of network measurements. This falls under the domain of machine learning and artificial intelligence, which is covered by several sub-categories in arXiv CS. The paper introduces a novel explainable AI approach, which allows to understand the reasons leading to a particular decision of a supervised learning-based model, additionally extending its application to the unsupervised learning domain. This suggests that the paper could belong to several sub-categories, including cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Among these, cs.LG and cs.NE are the most likely sub-categories, as they deal with machine learning and clustering techniques, which are the main focus of the paper. The other sub-categories are also relevant, as they cover topics such as security, explainable AI, and social networks, which are mentioned in the paper.
